lementor-element-51bb368 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"51bb368\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Basics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Full Thickness Intussusception of the Rectal Wall Through the Anus<\/li><li>20% Have Concurrent Cystocele or Uterine Prolapse<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Risk Factors<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Female<\/li><li>Elderly<\/li><li>Prior Pregnancy<\/li><li>Chronic Strain<\/li><li>Chronic Constipation\/Diarrhea<\/li><li>Psychiatric Disorders<\/li><li>Redundant Sigmoid<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Symptoms<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Physical Prolapse<\/li><li>Rectal Pain\/Pressure<\/li><li>Blood\/Mucous Drainage<\/li><li>Fecal Incontinence<\/li><li>Constipation<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Workup<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Diagnosis: Physical Exam<ul><li>Concentric Circular Folds\/Rings (Differentiates from Hemorrhoids)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Preoperative Workup:<ul><li>Colonoscopy (Rule Out CA)<\/li><li>Defecography (Evaluate Anatomy\/Function)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Acute Prolapse: <strong>Reduce<\/strong><ul><li>Adjuncts:<ul><li>Table Sugar (Absorbs Excess Water &amp; Reduce Edema)<\/li><li>Perianal Muscle Paralysis<\/li><li>General Anesthesia (Relaxation)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>If Strangulated: Emergent Surgery<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Chronic Prolapse:<ul><li>Peds: Medical Management (Fiber)<\/li><li>Adults: Surgery if Able<ul><li>Medical Management if Unfit for Surgery<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Surgical Approach<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Healthy\/Low-Risk: <strong>Transabdominal Procedure (LAR<\/strong> &amp; <strong>Colonopexy)<\/strong><\/li><li>Frail\/High-Risk: <strong>Perineal Procedure<\/strong><ul><li><a href=\"http:\/\/operativereview.com\/rectal-prolapse-procedures\/\">*See Anorectal: Rectal Prolapse Procedures<\/a><\/li><li>Higher Recurrence but Lower Morbidity<\/li><li>Procedure:<ul><li>Short Segment (&lt; 5 cm): <em>Delorme\u2019s Procedure<\/em><\/li><li>Long Segment (&gt; 5 cm): <em>Altemeier\u2019s Procedure<\/em> <a class=\"button\" style=\"background-color: #193556; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 2px;\" href=\"#MN\">Mn <\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>If Recurs: Can Repeat Perineal Procedure (Must Include Prior Anastomosis in Resected Specimen)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5556aaa\" data-id=\"5556aaa\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4cb5069 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"4cb5069\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-11520 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Rectal-Prolapse.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Rectal-Prolapse.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Rectal-Prolapse-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Rectal Prolapse <sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e6f5d34 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e6f5d34\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div clas